Come on, meet him.

1346
00:58:33,429 --> 00:58:35,431
Not right now.

1347
00:58:35,932 --> 00:58:36,933
Max is an amazing man.

1348
00:58:36,933 --> 00:58:39,436
Yeah, I'm sure.
Maybe later.

1349
00:58:41,939 --> 00:58:43,941
So who's Glen?

1350
00:58:47,945 --> 00:58:49,446
He's a nice guy.

1351
00:58:49,446 --> 00:58:50,447
Oh, yeah?

1352
00:58:50,447 --> 00:58:52,950
Yeah, he's just a nice guy.

1353
00:58:55,953 --> 00:58:57,454
What do you want, Sam?

1354
00:59:01,457 --> 00:59:02,959
Serena, listen.

1355
00:59:02,959 --> 00:59:05,462
I have to get him
to Las Vegas. My giant.

1356
00:59:05,462 --> 00:59:06,965
There's a movie
that's shooting there.

1357
00:59:06,965 --> 00:59:08,466
Nicky actually told me
about it.

1358
00:59:08,466 --> 00:59:09,467
I spoke to
the casting director.

1359
00:59:09,968 --> 00:59:10,468
If I can get Max there--

1360
00:59:10,969 --> 00:59:11,469
No money, Sam.

1361
00:59:11,970 --> 00:59:13,471
Did I say money?

1362
00:59:13,972 --> 00:59:15,973
What else would you
be talking about?

1363
00:59:15,973 --> 00:59:17,475
Not money. You did not
hear me say the words

1364
00:59:17,475 --> 00:59:18,476
"I want money."

1365
00:59:18,476 --> 00:59:19,477
I'd recognize my voice.

1366
00:59:19,477 --> 00:59:21,980
I did not say I want money.

1367
00:59:21,980 --> 00:59:23,982
I need the rings.

1368
00:59:23,982 --> 00:59:26,485
The rings.

1369
00:59:26,986 --> 00:59:28,988
They were my father's
and they were given to me.

1370
00:59:29,488 --> 00:59:31,489
For safekeeping.
To be given to your son.

1371
00:59:31,990 --> 00:59:32,490
They're called heirlooms.

1372
00:59:32,991 --> 00:59:33,992
I need to borrow them.

1373
00:59:34,492 --> 00:59:35,995
They're Nicky's.

1374
00:59:35,995 --> 00:59:37,997
I'm broke.

1375
00:59:37,997 --> 00:59:41,000
OK? I have nothing.

1376
00:59:41,000 --> 00:59:42,501
I am busted.

1377
00:59:42,501 --> 00:59:45,504
I'll get 'em back to you.

1378
00:59:45,504 --> 00:59:49,008
You know the funny thing, Sam,

1379
00:59:49,008 --> 00:59:52,011
I thought you came here
because you missed us.

1380
00:59:52,011 --> 00:59:55,013
That's why I thought
you came with...

1381
00:59:55,013 --> 00:59:56,015
your giant.

1382
00:59:56,515 --> 00:59:59,018
Serena, Serena.
I miss you.

1383
00:59:59,018 --> 01:00:00,518
Of course I miss you.

1384
01:00:00,518 --> 01:00:02,520
Mom?

1385
01:00:02,520 --> 01:00:05,024
Give dad the rings.

1386
01:00:05,024 --> 01:00:07,026
I don't need them.

1387
01:00:16,253 --> 01:00:17,254
You buy something, Sam?

1388
01:00:17,254 --> 01:00:18,755
Yeah, bus fare.

1389
01:00:19,256 --> 01:00:20,757
Taxi!

1390
01:00:20,757 --> 01:00:21,758
Come on.

1391
01:00:24,262 --> 01:00:26,264
An adult and a child
for Las Vegas, please.

1392
01:00:26,264 --> 01:00:29,267
I'm kidding.
2 for Las Vegas, please.

1393
01:00:29,767 --> 01:00:30,267
Galoop, Sam.

1394
01:00:30,767 --> 01:00:31,768
First Vegas, then Galoop.

1395
01:00:31,768 --> 01:00:32,769
But you say--

1396
01:00:32,769 --> 01:00:33,770
Max, please, please.

1397
01:00:33,770 --> 01:00:34,772
2 for Las Vegas.

1398
01:00:34,772 --> 01:00:36,774
Galoop.

1399
01:00:36,774 --> 01:00:39,777
Give us a second, please?

1400
01:00:39,777 --> 01:00:42,280
Come over here.

1401
01:00:42,280 --> 01:00:45,283
We have to go to Las Vegas first.

1402
01:00:45,283 --> 01:00:46,784
We go to Vegas first.

1403
01:00:46,784 --> 01:00:48,286
It's on the way to Galoop.

1404
01:00:48,286 --> 01:00:49,787
The movie is in Las Vegas,

1405
01:00:50,288 --> 01:00:51,289
And we don't want
to be messing around.

1406
01:00:51,789 --> 01:00:54,292
I want to see Lillianna first.

1407
01:00:55,293 --> 01:00:56,794
Sit down.

1408
01:00:58,796 --> 01:01:00,297
Sit down.

1409
01:01:00,297 --> 01:01:02,299
Are you famous yet?

1410
01:01:02,299 --> 01:01:03,801
I don't know.

1411
01:01:03,801 --> 01:01:04,802
What did we say?

1412
01:01:04,802 --> 01:01:06,304
We said you'd meet her
when you were famous.

1413
01:01:06,304 --> 01:01:07,805
That was the agreement.

1414
01:01:07,805 --> 01:01:09,307
When will I be famous?

1415
01:01:12,310 --> 01:01:14,312
OK, we'll call her.

1416
01:01:14,312 --> 01:01:15,313
OK? We'll call her.

1417
01:01:15,313 --> 01:01:16,314
We'll tell her
that you're here,

1418
01:01:16,314 --> 01:01:17,815
That you're on your
way to see her, OK?

1419
01:01:17,815 --> 01:01:19,317
We can do?

1420
01:01:23,822 --> 01:01:25,824
Max, this is just a letter.

1421
01:01:25,824 --> 01:01:27,326
This is just her address.

1422
01:01:27,326 --> 01:01:28,828
There's no phone number here.

1423
01:01:28,828 --> 01:01:30,329
We no can call?

1424
01:01:32,832 --> 01:01:34,334
We'll call information.

1425
01:01:34,334 --> 01:01:36,336
Right? We'll call Information.

1426
01:01:36,336 --> 01:01:38,338
Is she still living here?

1427
01:01:38,838 --> 01:01:40,340
When was the last time
she wrote to you?

1428
01:01:40,340 --> 01:01:41,341
She don't write.

1429
01:01:41,842 --> 01:01:43,344
She don't write?

1430
01:01:43,344 --> 01:01:44,344
No.

1431
01:01:44,344 --> 01:01:46,346
Never?

1432
01:01:46,346 --> 01:01:48,348
And you've been
writing to her for...

1433
01:01:48,348 --> 01:01:49,849
22 years.

1434
01:01:51,851 --> 01:01:54,321
In Galoop... in Gallup,

1435
01:01:54,321 --> 01:01:55,805
Miss Lillianna Otarro,

1436
01:01:55,805 --> 01:01:58,308
231 Desert View Place.

1437
01:01:58,807 --> 01:02:00,809
It's a good thing you have
a relationship with god, Max.

1438
01:02:00,809 --> 01:02:02,312
We may need his Rolodex.

1439
01:02:02,312 --> 01:02:03,813
What?

1440
01:02:03,813 --> 01:02:07,317
An L.J. Otarro
on Wonder View Terrace.

1441
01:02:07,317 --> 01:02:09,319
All right,
let's try that.

1442
01:02:09,319 --> 01:02:11,822
Could you connect me?
Thank you.

1443
01:02:12,323 --> 01:02:13,823
Max, don't get
your hopes up.

1444
01:02:13,823 --> 01:02:16,326
It may not be
the right person.

1445
01:02:16,326 --> 01:02:17,327
You never know about
these things, you know?

1446
01:02:17,327 --> 01:02:18,328
Hello.

1447
01:02:18,328 --> 01:02:20,831
Hello.

1448
01:02:20,831 --> 01:02:22,333
Who's calling?

1449
01:02:22,333 --> 01:02:23,834
One second, please.

1450
01:02:23,834 --> 01:02:24,835
Do you want to talk?

1451
01:02:24,835 --> 01:02:26,337
No, no, no, no, no.

1452
01:02:27,838 --> 01:02:29,339
Is this Lillianna Otarro?

1453
01:02:29,339 --> 01:02:30,841
Yes.

1454
01:02:31,342 --> 01:02:33,344
Are you from Romania?

1455
01:02:33,344 --> 01:02:34,845
Yes.

1456
01:02:34,845 --> 01:02:37,848
I have a giant surprise
for you.

1457
01:02:37,848 --> 01:02:42,355
I'm calling for your old
friend Maximus Sanferescu.

1458
01:02:43,855 --> 01:02:48,859
He's in Chicago right now
and yes, he is,

1459
01:02:48,859 --> 01:02:51,863
but he's on his way to
Las Vegas to be in a movie.

1460
01:02:51,863 --> 01:02:53,865
Yes, he's an actor.

1461
01:02:53,865 --> 01:02:56,368
Please hang up.
This is a recording.

1462
01:02:56,368 --> 01:02:57,868
He's crazy about you.

1463
01:02:57,868 --> 01:03:00,372
I agree.
He remembers that kiss.

1464
01:03:03,375 --> 01:03:05,377
Right, behind the
fountain of the virgin.

1465
01:03:05,377 --> 01:03:08,380
Well, you didn't forget
it either, did you?

1466
01:03:09,382 --> 01:03:12,385
Well, he would like
to come visit you.

1467
01:03:12,385 --> 01:03:14,386
Oh, that's a bummer.

1468
01:03:14,386 --> 01:03:16,888
Oh, for how long?

1469
01:03:16,888 --> 01:03:19,892
Couple of days.
Well, listen, Lillianna,

1470
01:03:19,892 --> 01:03:21,894
We will call you
and we'll--we'll hook up

1471
01:03:21,894 --> 01:03:23,896
in Gallup, OK?

1472
01:03:23,896 --> 01:03:26,899
It was lovely talking
to you, too, Lillianna.

1473
01:03:26,899 --> 01:03:29,402
I will tell him. OK.

1474
01:03:29,402 --> 01:03:31,404
All right. Good-bye.

1475
01:03:31,404 --> 01:03:32,405
Here.

1476
01:03:32,405 --> 01:03:33,406
She wants to see me?

1477
01:03:33,406 --> 01:03:34,907
Yes, but she's gonna be gone

1478
01:03:34,907 --> 01:03:36,409
for a couple of days.

1479
01:03:36,409 --> 01:03:37,911
But she want to see me?

1480
01:03:37,911 --> 01:03:40,914
Yeah, Max. How could
she not? Come on.

1481
01:03:40,914 --> 01:03:41,915
And the kiss, Sam?

1482
01:03:41,915 --> 01:03:44,417
What she say about the kiss?

1483
01:03:44,417 --> 01:03:45,918
That she'll never forget it.

1484
01:03:46,418 --> 01:03:47,419
Come on.

1485
01:03:47,920 --> 01:03:49,422
Oh, Sam.

1486
01:03:50,923 --> 01:03:53,427
Yep, that's what she said.

1487
01:03:53,427 --> 01:03:55,429
I'm so happy.

1488
01:03:57,931 --> 01:03:59,433
Isn't that nice?

1489
01:04:02,936 --> 01:04:04,438
- Sam?
- Yeah.

1490
01:04:04,438 --> 01:04:06,940
Tell me again. What
she say about the kiss?

1491
01:04:06,940 --> 01:04:08,943
Max, you know what she said.

1492
01:04:08,943 --> 01:04:10,445
That she never forget.

1493
01:04:10,445 --> 01:04:12,946
That's right.

1494
01:04:12,946 --> 01:04:14,448
Thank you.

1495
01:04:43,478 --> 01:04:45,980
Max? Max, wake up.

1496
01:04:45,980 --> 01:04:46,981
What?

1497
01:04:46,981 --> 01:04:48,983
I want you to see something.

1498
01:04:48,983 --> 01:04:51,486
Look.

1499
01:04:54,489 --> 01:04:56,491
It is miracle.

1500
01:04:56,491 --> 01:04:59,494
The miracle is we got here.

1501
01:05:05,501 --> 01:05:08,505
Wait till you see
the buffets, Max.

1502
01:05:08,505 --> 01:05:11,507
Do the words
"all you can eat"

1503
01:05:11,507 --> 01:05:14,510
mean anything to you?

1504
01:05:14,510 --> 01:05:16,513
Hey, hey, hey!

1505
01:05:24,522 --> 01:05:27,023
This is show business, Max.

1506
01:05:37,034 --> 01:05:38,536
And... cut!

1507
01:05:38,536 --> 01:05:40,037
That's a cut!

1508
01:05:40,037 --> 01:05:41,037
OK, great.

1509
01:05:41,037 --> 01:05:42,538
OK, come on, guys,
gather around.

1510
01:05:42,538 --> 01:05:44,541
Steven, that was really
great, but I think

1511
01:05:44,541 --> 01:05:47,043
We can do just a little
bit better, don't you?

1512
01:05:47,043 --> 01:05:48,044
No.

1513
01:05:48,044 --> 01:05:49,546
OK, that was perfect, everybody.

1514
01:05:50,046 --> 01:05:51,481
New deal.
We're moving on.

1515
01:05:51,581 --> 01:05:53,049
What do you mean,
"cast"?

1516
01:05:53,049 --> 01:05:54,552
It wasn't cast
a couple of days ago!

1517
01:05:54,552 --> 01:05:55,552
Please.

1518
01:05:55,552 --> 01:05:57,053
But I called!
We came all this way!

1519
01:05:57,554 --> 01:05:59,055
I asked specifically,
"Do you need a big villain?"

1520
01:05:59,055 --> 01:06:01,057
'Cause that's what I got!
I got the biggest!

1521
01:06:01,057 --> 01:06:02,058
We don't need, capisce?
Case closed.

1522
01:06:02,058 --> 01:06:03,561
- Can I at least show him to you?
- No.

1523
01:06:03,561 --> 01:06:04,562
Let me show him to the director.

1524
01:06:04,562 --> 01:06:06,564
Don't bother him.
We're in a meal penalty.

1525
01:06:06,564 --> 01:06:08,065
You tell me I'm wrong
and I go away.

1526
01:06:08,566 --> 01:06:10,067
But if Steven Seagal
finds out

1527
01:06:10,067 --> 01:06:11,067
That you blew this opportunity,

1528
01:06:11,067 --> 01:06:12,068
it's on your head.

1529
01:06:12,068 --> 01:06:13,070
How big is he?

1530
01:06:13,571 --> 01:06:14,572
Around 8 feet and he can act.
You got a script?

1531
01:06:14,572 --> 01:06:15,573
No lines.

1532
01:06:15,573 --> 01:06:17,074
The bad guy's just an action part.
Excuse me.

1533
01:06:17,575 --> 01:06:19,077
That's perfect, 'cause,
now, what do you need?

1534
01:06:19,077 --> 01:06:21,079
You need a big, scary guy
and that's what I have.

1535
01:06:21,079 --> 01:06:23,082
The biggest and scariest
guy of all time,

1536
01:06:23,082 --> 01:06:24,584
and he's sitting
right over there.

1537
01:06:24,584 --> 01:06:27,085
Max, stand up!

1538
01:06:27,085 --> 01:06:28,587
All the way up.
Don't slouch.

1539
01:06:29,087 --> 01:06:30,589
How about that, guys?

1540
01:06:30,589 --> 01:06:32,090
Big enough?

1541
01:06:32,090 --> 01:06:33,092
He's unbelievable!

1542
01:06:33,092 --> 01:06:34,594
Oh, yeah, you see?
He's big.

1543
01:06:37,096 --> 01:06:39,098
Mr. Seagal, this is...
a pleasure to meet you.

1544
01:06:39,098 --> 01:06:40,598
I'm Sam Kamin.
I'm Max the giant's agent.

1545
01:06:41,098 --> 01:06:43,101
You... have your
elbow in his salad.

1546
01:06:44,603 --> 01:06:45,604
Sorry.

1547
01:06:45,604 --> 01:06:47,606
Steven, what do you think
about him as the bad guy?

1548
01:06:47,606 --> 01:06:48,607
The fact of the matter is

1549
01:06:48,607 --> 01:06:49,608
that he's much bigger than me

1550
01:06:49,608 --> 01:06:50,609
and as you know,
that's not good.

1551
01:06:51,109 --> 01:06:51,611
- Good.
- May I, sir?

1552
01:06:52,111 --> 01:06:53,112
Isn't that actually the point?

1553
01:06:53,112 --> 01:06:54,614
I don't think so.

1554
01:06:54,614 --> 01:06:56,615
No, see, I have this theory
about heroes and villains--

1555
01:06:56,615 --> 01:06:59,117
I know. Look, let's
not forget about Roy.

1556
01:06:59,117 --> 01:07:00,118
I mean, the fact
of the matter is

1557
01:07:00,118 --> 01:07:01,119
we did offer him
the part.

1558
01:07:01,621 --> 01:07:02,121
That's right.
There's Roy.

1559
01:07:02,622 --> 01:07:03,122
Who's Roy?

1560
01:07:03,623 --> 01:07:04,624
Steven's best friend.

1561
01:07:04,624 --> 01:07:06,626
He's our head stuntman
and he's got the role.

1562
01:07:06,626 --> 01:07:08,127
Come on, he's a stuntman.

1563
01:07:08,127 --> 01:07:10,128
With all due respect,
probably a great one,

1564
01:07:10,128 --> 01:07:11,631
but now, stuntmen stunt.

1565
01:07:11,631 --> 01:07:13,633
He acts! My giant
can do Shakespeare!

1566
01:07:13,633 --> 01:07:15,134
Shakespeare.

1567
01:07:15,134 --> 01:07:17,136
Every word.

1568
01:07:17,136 --> 01:07:18,638
I've always wanted
to do Shakespeare.

1569
01:07:18,638 --> 01:07:20,139
You would be a great
Shakespearean actor.

1570
01:07:20,139 --> 01:07:21,642
Matter of fact,
you and Max together

1571
01:07:22,142 --> 01:07:23,644
in this movie...
would be great

1572
01:07:23,644 --> 01:07:25,645
doing Shakespeare together.
Can you see it?

1573
01:07:25,645 --> 01:07:27,146
No. This is
a story about a man

1574
01:07:27,146 --> 01:07:28,147
who's trying
to stop terrorists

1575
01:07:28,147 --> 01:07:29,649
from blowing up
the Las Vegas strip.

1576
01:07:29,649 --> 01:07:30,651
Now if you'll excuse me--

1577
01:07:30,651 --> 01:07:32,153
But, sir...

1578
01:07:32,153 --> 01:07:33,655
You don't see how Shakespeare

1579
01:07:33,655 --> 01:07:35,156
can fall into that script idea?

1580
01:07:35,156 --> 01:07:36,658
- No. - Oh, come on!
It's easy!

1581
01:07:37,158 --> 01:07:38,158
You got this huge villain,

1582
01:07:38,158 --> 01:07:39,158
the world's biggest terrorist.

1583
01:07:39,659 --> 01:07:40,160
He's huge.

1584
01:07:40,661 --> 01:07:41,662
- Scary.
- Oh, scary.

1585
01:07:42,162 --> 01:07:43,163
And he's planting bombs

1586
01:07:43,163 --> 01:07:44,665
all over the strip, right?

1587
01:07:44,665 --> 01:07:46,667
But he's sending
messages to you...

1588
01:07:46,667 --> 01:07:48,168
in Iambic pentameter.

1589
01:07:48,168 --> 01:07:49,169
Great.

1590
01:07:49,169 --> 01:07:50,672
If he can eliminate you...

1591
01:07:50,672 --> 01:07:52,173
with the Shakespeare...

1592
01:07:52,173 --> 01:07:53,174
See, he can be "to be"

1593
01:07:53,174 --> 01:07:54,174
and you are "not to be"

1594
01:07:54,174 --> 01:07:55,175
because he doesn't
want you to be.

1595
01:07:55,676 --> 01:07:56,176
Right.

1596
01:07:56,677 --> 01:07:57,678
But you have to stop that, see?

1597
01:07:57,678 --> 01:07:58,679
Because he loves Shakespeare

1598
01:07:59,179 --> 01:08:00,682
and blowing up stuff.

1599
01:08:00,682 --> 01:08:02,183
Max, do Henry V.

1600
01:08:02,183 --> 01:08:03,184
What?

1601
01:08:03,184 --> 01:08:04,686
Do Henry V!
He's...

1602
01:08:04,686 --> 01:08:06,688
You don't like it, Sam.
Remember?

1603
01:08:06,688 --> 01:08:08,189
We got to get back to work.

1604
01:08:08,189 --> 01:08:09,691
Wait, wait, wait,
wait a second.

1605
01:08:09,691 --> 01:08:11,192
Max, listen to me.

1606
01:08:11,192 --> 01:08:13,695
