Go away.

1869
01:20:23,664 --> 01:20:25,165
Please, don't do this, Lillianna.

1870
01:20:25,165 --> 01:20:26,167
How do you know my name?

1871
01:20:26,167 --> 01:20:27,669
I'm a friend of
Maximus Sanferescu.

1872
01:20:28,169 --> 01:20:29,169
You're the one
who was calling?

1873
01:20:29,169 --> 01:20:31,171
Yes.
Max is very sick...

1874
01:20:31,171 --> 01:20:32,673
...and he needs to see you.

1875
01:20:32,673 --> 01:20:34,174
I know he is sick.

1876
01:20:34,174 --> 01:20:36,678
He's very sick.
He's obsessed with me.

1877
01:20:36,678 --> 01:20:37,679
Do you know how many letters

1878
01:20:37,679 --> 01:20:39,180
I've gotten from him
in 20 years?

1879
01:20:39,180 --> 01:20:40,181
Maybe 1,000...

1880
01:20:40,181 --> 01:20:41,683
until I told
the post office

1881
01:20:41,683 --> 01:20:42,684
to start destroying them.

1882
01:20:42,684 --> 01:20:43,684
It's called stalking.

1883
01:20:43,684 --> 01:20:45,687
Does he know
it's against the law?

1884
01:20:45,687 --> 01:20:46,688
I could get you
both arrested.

1885
01:20:47,188 --> 01:20:48,189
Let me explain,
please.

1886
01:20:48,189 --> 01:20:50,192
Explain why the church
doesn't do something

1887
01:20:50,192 --> 01:20:51,193
about this perverted priest.

1888
01:20:51,193 --> 01:20:52,695
Explain that to me.

1889
01:20:53,195 --> 01:20:54,196
Wait a second.
He is not a pervert.

1890
01:20:54,698 --> 01:20:55,699
He's not even a priest.

1891
01:20:56,199 --> 01:20:58,201
He's a good man.
He's a wonderful man

1892
01:20:58,201 --> 01:20:59,201
who's in love with you

1893
01:20:59,201 --> 01:21:00,703
and he's always been
in love with you.

1894
01:21:01,203 --> 01:21:02,705
He remembers kissing you.

1895
01:21:02,705 --> 01:21:04,708
I never kissed him.

1896
01:21:04,708 --> 01:21:05,709
In Lunca?

1897
01:21:05,709 --> 01:21:06,710
Behind the fountain
of the virgin

1898
01:21:06,710 --> 01:21:08,211
at the end of the road

1899
01:21:08,211 --> 01:21:10,713
near his parents'
house? Right?

1900
01:21:10,713 --> 01:21:13,716
That was 20 years ago.

1901
01:21:13,716 --> 01:21:16,218
I was a kid. There's
nothing to talk about.

1902
01:21:16,719 --> 01:21:17,720
Wait...

1903
01:21:17,720 --> 01:21:19,722
Lillianna, he's
an unusual person.

1904
01:21:19,722 --> 01:21:21,223
If you would let me explain,

1905
01:21:21,724 --> 01:21:22,725
you'd understand.

1906
01:21:22,725 --> 01:21:24,227
All I'm asking

1907
01:21:24,227 --> 01:21:26,229
is for you to give me
5 minutes, OK?

1908
01:21:26,229 --> 01:21:27,731
Just 5 minutes.

1909
01:21:27,731 --> 01:21:28,731
You come into this restaurant--

1910
01:21:29,231 --> 01:21:30,232
in public--

1911
01:21:30,232 --> 01:21:32,234
Sit down, have a cup
of coffee with me

1912
01:21:32,234 --> 01:21:34,738
and listen to what
I have to say about Max.

1913
01:21:34,738 --> 01:21:36,239
There are things
that you don't know

1914
01:21:36,239 --> 01:21:38,742
that'll make all the
difference in the world.

1915
01:21:38,742 --> 01:21:39,743
Please.

1916
01:21:39,743 --> 01:21:41,745
5 minutes?

1917
01:21:42,245 --> 01:21:44,247
What do you say?

1918
01:21:44,247 --> 01:21:46,750
I don't want to.
Get away from my car.

1919
01:22:01,682 --> 01:22:02,184
'Allo?

1920
01:22:02,684 --> 01:22:03,185
Max, it's me.

1921
01:22:03,685 --> 01:22:04,186
Sammy!

1922
01:22:04,686 --> 01:22:06,188
Did you see her?

1923
01:22:06,188 --> 01:22:07,689
Not only
did I see her,

1924
01:22:07,689 --> 01:22:10,191
I'm bringing her
to the hotel.

1925
01:22:10,191 --> 01:22:11,192
She's coming?

1926
01:22:11,192 --> 01:22:12,693
Any second.

1927
01:22:12,693 --> 01:22:13,694
What did she say?

1928
01:22:14,195 --> 01:22:14,695
Now, listen,

1929
01:22:15,196 --> 01:22:16,697
In 20 years, people change.

1930
01:22:16,697 --> 01:22:17,698
You understand?

1931
01:22:17,698 --> 01:22:18,699
So don't be surprised

1932
01:22:18,699 --> 01:22:20,701
if you find her a
little bit changed.

1933
01:22:20,701 --> 01:22:21,703
What do I wear?

1934
01:22:21,703 --> 01:22:23,705
Stay away from
vertical stripes.

1935
01:22:25,207 --> 01:22:29,710
What if she don't like me
when she see me?

1936
01:22:29,710 --> 01:22:31,213
She will like you,
Max.

1937
01:22:31,713 --> 01:22:33,215
Trust me.

1938
01:22:34,716 --> 01:22:36,718
I'll see you in
a few minutes, OK?

1939
01:22:37,219 --> 01:22:38,220
All right. Bye.

1940
01:22:46,228 --> 01:22:48,730
Lillianna,
I'm gonna tell Max

1941
01:22:48,730 --> 01:22:50,733
that you're here, OK?
Thanks.

1942
01:22:55,738 --> 01:22:56,738
Hey...

1943
01:22:58,740 --> 01:22:59,741
Are you ready?

1944
01:22:59,741 --> 01:23:01,244
She's here?

1945
01:23:01,244 --> 01:23:02,245
She's here.

1946
01:23:02,245 --> 01:23:04,247
I'll bring her in, OK?

1947
01:23:04,247 --> 01:23:05,248
Yes.

1948
01:23:08,750 --> 01:23:11,753
Lillianna,
You wanna... come in?

1949
01:23:20,764 --> 01:23:23,267
Come in.
He won't bite.

1950
01:23:30,274 --> 01:23:31,775
Lillianna...

1951
01:23:31,775 --> 01:23:33,277
Maximus...

1952
01:23:39,784 --> 01:23:44,288
Max, Lillianna would like it
if you spoke English.

1953
01:23:44,788 --> 01:23:45,789
Yes. Please.

1954
01:23:45,789 --> 01:23:47,791
Yes. English.

1955
01:23:50,295 --> 01:23:51,296
We all speak English.

1956
01:23:58,303 --> 01:23:59,804
Listen, if you two
would like me to go--

1957
01:24:00,305 --> 01:24:00,805
- No.
- No.

1958
01:24:01,306 --> 01:24:02,807
I'll be happy to stay.

1959
01:24:02,807 --> 01:24:04,808
I'll just...
be right there.

1960
01:24:18,823 --> 01:24:20,325
You look different.

1961
01:24:21,826 --> 01:24:23,328
And you.

1962
01:24:23,328 --> 01:24:25,330
I grow.

1963
01:24:25,330 --> 01:24:27,332
Yes.

1964
01:24:27,332 --> 01:24:28,834
Too much.

1965
01:24:28,834 --> 01:24:32,338
You are still my Maximus.

1966
01:24:38,345 --> 01:24:40,346
Why you never write to me?

1967
01:24:42,348 --> 01:24:43,849
I wanted to,

1968
01:24:43,849 --> 01:24:44,850
But... my--

1969
01:24:45,351 --> 01:24:45,851
father.

1970
01:24:46,352 --> 01:24:47,354
Father was so strict.

1971
01:24:47,854 --> 01:24:49,356
I'm sorry.

1972
01:24:49,856 --> 01:24:51,358
I thought you forgot me.

1973
01:24:51,858 --> 01:24:52,359
No.

1974
01:24:52,859 --> 01:24:53,360
You remembered?

1975
01:24:53,860 --> 01:24:54,861
Everything.

1976
01:24:54,861 --> 01:24:57,364
Goat boy and the treasure?

1977
01:24:57,364 --> 01:24:58,865
The treasure?

1978
01:24:58,865 --> 01:25:01,868
Yeah. The goat.
Mine jump up.

1979
01:25:01,868 --> 01:25:05,371
The goat.

1980
01:25:05,871 --> 01:25:07,374
That was so funny.

1981
01:25:07,374 --> 01:25:09,875
When the machine
cut his legs off?

1982
01:25:09,875 --> 01:25:12,378
That was so sad.

1983
01:25:12,378 --> 01:25:14,380
I wrote to you
every day.

1984
01:25:14,880 --> 01:25:17,384
I sent you poems.

1985
01:25:17,384 --> 01:25:20,387
I remember every one.

1986
01:25:20,387 --> 01:25:21,388
Say one.

1987
01:25:23,390 --> 01:25:24,890
Say one.

1988
01:25:24,890 --> 01:25:26,893
Whichever you like best.

1989
01:25:27,394 --> 01:25:27,894
Max,

1990
01:25:28,395 --> 01:25:29,396
why don't you do

1991
01:25:29,396 --> 01:25:30,897
one of your favorite poems
for Lillianna?

1992
01:25:30,897 --> 01:25:33,400
Wouldn't you like to hear
one, Lillianna, from Max?

1993
01:25:33,400 --> 01:25:34,401
Yes, please.

1994
01:25:34,401 --> 01:25:36,904
I've longed to hear
one in your voice.

1995
01:25:36,904 --> 01:25:38,907
No. My accent.

1996
01:25:39,408 --> 01:25:40,908
Is beautiful.

1997
01:25:40,908 --> 01:25:43,911
Nothing about me
is beautiful.

1998
01:25:56,925 --> 01:25:58,927
Please.

1999
01:26:12,940 --> 01:26:15,944
How do I love thee?

2000
01:26:15,944 --> 01:26:18,447
Let me count the ways.

2001
01:26:18,447 --> 01:26:24,453
I love thee to the depth
and breadth and height

2002
01:26:24,453 --> 01:26:25,454
My soul can reach.

2003
01:26:25,454 --> 01:26:32,461
I love thee with
the breaths, smiles, tears

2004
01:26:32,461 --> 01:26:34,964
For all my life.

2005
01:26:34,964 --> 01:26:36,966
And if god chooses,

2006
01:26:36,966 --> 01:26:41,470
I shall love thee better
after death.

2007
01:26:57,488 --> 01:27:01,491
You are happy,
Lillianna, in your life?

2008
01:27:03,994 --> 01:27:05,996
You're alone?

2009
01:27:07,998 --> 01:27:09,499
You are married.

2010
01:27:13,003 --> 01:27:14,505
He is a good man?

2011
01:27:16,006 --> 01:27:18,509
He doesn't seem to know it,

2012
01:27:18,509 --> 01:27:20,511
but he's a good man.

2013
01:27:20,511 --> 01:27:24,515
He just doesn't
feel good enough.

2014
01:27:24,515 --> 01:27:27,518
Even with your love?

2015
01:27:30,020 --> 01:27:33,024
You deserve better man.

2016
01:27:35,527 --> 01:27:39,530
Lillianna,
you remember the kiss?

2017
01:27:39,530 --> 01:27:42,033
Behind the fountain?

2018
01:27:42,033 --> 01:27:44,035
Yes.

2019
01:27:44,035 --> 01:27:46,037
I will never forget it.

2020
01:27:46,037 --> 01:27:48,540
I still dream of it.

2021
01:28:18,070 --> 01:28:21,074
I'm so sorry, but...

2022
01:28:21,074 --> 01:28:24,076
We will always
have the sunset.

2023
01:28:38,591 --> 01:28:43,096
Just know...
I will never forget you.

2024
01:28:58,612 --> 01:29:00,113
I'll be right back.

2025
01:29:08,705 --> 01:29:10,707
Do you want me to go
to the airport with you?

2026
01:29:10,707 --> 01:29:13,710
No. I think you should
stay with him.

2027
01:29:17,715 --> 01:29:19,718
Do you have to go
right away?

2028
01:29:19,718 --> 01:29:21,220
It's Nicky's birthday.

2029
01:29:21,719 --> 01:29:23,221
Yeah.

2030
01:29:25,223 --> 01:29:27,726
That was unbelievable.
That was really amazing.

2031
01:29:28,227 --> 01:29:29,228
The kiss, however,
I didn't see coming--

2032
01:29:29,228 --> 01:29:30,229
Sammy.

2033
01:29:30,229 --> 01:29:32,231
Yeah?

2034
01:29:34,733 --> 01:29:36,235
Right.

2035
01:29:40,739 --> 01:29:42,241
Thank you.

2036
01:29:44,243 --> 01:29:46,745
That meant everything to him.

2037
01:29:46,745 --> 01:29:48,248
And me.

2038
01:29:49,249 --> 01:29:54,252
And me. You know,
what you did for him...

2039
01:29:55,753 --> 01:29:58,257
That's the man
I married.

2040
01:29:59,758 --> 01:30:02,261
I've missed you.

2041
01:30:10,769 --> 01:30:13,772
Hey, Serena...

2042
01:30:13,772 --> 01:30:15,774
You're my Lillianna.

2043
01:30:16,276 --> 01:30:19,279
I'm gonna love you forever.

2044
01:30:21,280 --> 01:30:24,283
There's one
big difference.

2045
01:30:27,787 --> 01:30:30,291
She didn't
love him back.

2046
01:31:15,520 --> 01:31:16,521
Spell, please.

2047
01:31:16,521 --> 01:31:20,007
Big back end?

2048
01:31:20,007 --> 01:31:23,010
Thank you.
I'll tell him. Good-bye.

2049
01:31:26,515 --> 01:31:29,017
What is "big back end"?

2050
01:31:29,017 --> 01:31:30,519
What?

2051
01:31:30,519 --> 01:31:32,020
The man
from the movie said,

2052
01:31:32,020 --> 01:31:34,023
"3-pic deal. Option TV.

2053
01:31:34,023 --> 01:31:36,024
Big back end."

2054
01:31:38,527 --> 01:31:40,028
What does this mean?

2055
01:31:42,031 --> 01:31:45,035
It means you're a star
of the silver screen, Max.

2056
01:31:45,536 --> 01:31:47,538
The biggest I ever had.

2057
01:31:48,038 --> 01:31:50,539
Seems like a perfect time
to leave, doesn't it?

2058
01:31:50,539 --> 01:31:52,541
Come on, pack up.

2059
01:31:54,043 --> 01:31:55,545
But the movie, Sam.

2060
01:31:57,046 --> 01:31:59,048
The movie's
the easy part, Max.

2061
01:31:59,048 --> 01:32:01,050
It's the deal that's hard.

2062
01:32:05,388 --> 01:32:07,390
So, I'm in Romania,

2063
01:32:07,390 --> 01:32:10,343
with a truly gigantic
movie star

2064
01:32:10,343 --> 01:32:11,344
whose one appearance

2065
01:32:11,344 --> 01:32:13,347
in a little-known European
movie skyrocketed him

2066
01:32:13,847 --> 01:32:15,849
to a 3-picture deal
in Hollywood.

2067
01:32:16,850 --> 01:32:20,853
But he got out
while he was still on top.

2068
01:33:53,415 --> 01:33:55,417
Good morning.

2069
01:33:56,418 --> 01:33:58,922
Sanferescu?

2070
01:34:07,430 --> 01:34:08,933
Max?

2071
01:34:08,933 --> 01:34:10,434
Max, wake up.

2072
01:34:15,940 --> 01:34:16,941
No!

2073
01:34:16,941 --> 01:34:19,443
No! Why you do this
to me, Sam?

2074
01:34:19,443 --> 01:34:21,445
Why?! Why you
bring me here?!

2075
01:34:21,445 --> 01:34:24,448
This is not my home!
They leave me!

2076
01:34:24,448 --> 01:34:25,950
Why, Sam?! Who tell you
do this to me?!

2077
01:34:33,958 --> 01:34:36,961
I told you lots of times,
I don't like this place!

2078
01:34:36,961 --> 01:34:38,964
My mother had a saying:

2079
01:34:38,964 --> 01:34:40,966
Never go to sleep angry.

2080
01:35:02,486 --> 01:35:03,487
Go home.

2081
01:35:40,527 --> 01:35:42,528
Mama.

2082
01:35:42,528 --> 01:35:44,530
Mama!

2083
01:35:57,044 --> 01:35:58,545
Dada.

2084
01:36:22,603 --> 01:36:25,607
I saw Max twice
over the next year.

2085
01:36:26,107 --> 01:36:29,611
The last time,
to say good-bye.

2086
01:36:29,611 --> 01:36:32,113
It's funny to think
that someone could die

2087
01:36:32,113 --> 01:36:37,119
because his heart was too big,
but that was Max.

2088
01:36:37,119 --> 01:36:39,120
The thing is,
he wanted to be small

2089
01:36:39,120 --> 01:36:41,623
and I wanted to be big.

2090
01:36:41,623 --> 01:36:43,124
But what we both
were looking for

2091
01:36:43,626 --> 01:36:45,127
had nothing
to do with size.

2092
01:36:45,627 --> 01:36:48,630
Because I'm not the tallest guy
in the world,

2093
01:36:48,630 --> 01:36:52,634
But in the eyes of my family,
I've become a giant.

2094
01:36:52,634 --> 01:36:57,139
Vanquish mine enemy!

2095
01:37:06,148 --> 01:37:07,650
Begone, foul demon,

2096
01:37:07,650 --> 01:37:09,652
For I am the swordmaster!

